body.body: Triumph Diagnostic Tool Development - Introduction of Login Service
Triumph are developing the Triumph Diagnostic Tool (TDT) to introduce a new login service.
The Login Service is being introduced to improve diagnostic tool security, and to prepare the software for future new features.
We currently estimate that the TDT Login Service will be rolled out to dealerships at the end of October 2023.
Upon rollout of the login service, users of the diagnostic tool will be required to login into the software using their Triumph Online user name and password.
What do I need to do?

To prepare for this, dealers are requested to ensure all staff that use the diagnostic tool are provided with their own Triumph Online account and email address. Diagnostic tool users will need their Triumph Online account to be setup and activated ahead of the TDT Login Service rollout date.
Dealers are also requested to ensure that their diagnostic tool computers have access to an internet connection in all areas where the diagnostic tool needs to be used.
The Triumph Diagnostic Tool User Guide will be updated to include information and instructions on how to use the Login service.
The user guide information for the Login service is also included below.
To access the diagnostic tool, users must login to the software using their triumphonline.net Username and Password.
Each individual diagnostic tool user will therefore need to have an active triumphonline.net account and an email address.
Triumph Online accounts can be managed from within the Triumph Online website. Login to triumphonline.net to manage your account and password.
Please contact your local Triumph Online administrator if you are experiencing any problems with your Triumph Online account.
Dealer Triumph Online users with admin access have the ability to manage the permission levels of the staff within their dealership.
To access the diagnostic tool each relevant user needs to have the Triumph Diagnostic Tool Access (TDT) permission enabled.
To enable Triumph Diagnostic Tool (TDT) access:
Navigate to the TOL User Management page shown above.
Select the User you wish to edit.
Within the Access Levels panel, expand the WOL drop down menu.
Make sure Triumph Diagnostic Tool (TDT) Access is ticked.
The TDT Access permission is now live and the user will be able to login to the TDT using their TOL username and password.
After launching the diagnostic software, the Login screen will be displayed.
Enter your triumphonline.net Username and Password and click
The Home Screen will be displayed.
To activate offline mode, you must first login to the diagnostic software while online.
Once activated, offline mode will be available to you for a period of 7 days from the point when the internet becomes disconnected.

The diagnostic software will remember the user who most recently logged into TDT online on a particular computer. This will allow that user to then login offline for up to 7 days using the same computer.
The diagnostic software cannot remember multiple users. Therefore, you will need to be online to login if you were not the most recent user to access the diagnostic software on a particular computer.
Log into the diagnostic software while online to activate Offline Mode for your user credentials.
When you are ready to use the diagnostic software offline, launch the software and login using your username and password as described above.
The Home screen will display your user details along with the amount of offline time you have remaining.
If your login fails for any reason (for example, due to an incorrect user name or password), the login screen will display a Login Failed message along with a brief explanation of the failure.
